  "hint": "Build a 3-layer tree: Layer 1 has four MUXes selecting (D0,D1), (D2,D3), (D4,D5), (D6,D7) using S0. Layer 2 has two MUXes selecting between layer-1 pairs using S1. Layer 3 has one final MUX selecting between layer-2 outputs using S2. Inputs: [D0..D7, S0, S1, S2].",
  "title": "8:1 MUX from 2:1 MUXes",
  "objective": "Build an 8-input multiplexer from a tree of seven 2:1 MUXes",
  "description": "Construct an 8:1 multiplexer using seven 2:1 MUXes arranged in a binary tree. Three select lines (S0, S1, S2) choose one of eight data inputs. This is how wide multiplexers are built in real datapaths — a key building block of register file read ports and ALU input selection.",
